---

Preheat the #oven{} to 400 degrees. Bring a #pot{} of water to a boil with a large
pinch of @salt{}. Halve the @grape tomatoes{1%bunch}. Thinly slice the
@garlic{2%cloves}. Finely chop the @parsley{1%bunch}. Trim the ends of the
@green beans{4%oz}.

Blanch the green beans by adding them to the boiling water for ~{1-2%minutes},
then set aside, reserving the water. Add the @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%oz} to the
boiling water and cook for ~{15-20%minutes}, until easily pierced with a knife.

Meanwhile, drizzle each @skin-on salmon fillet{2} with 1 teaspoon
@olive oil{1.5%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} on each side. Place on
a #baking sheet{}, skin side-down, and roast for ~{8-10%minutes}, until easily
flakes with a fork and slightly opaque in the middle. Drain the potatoes and
set aside.

Meanwhile, heat @butter{1%tbsp} in a pan over medium heat. Add the tomatoes and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook for about ~{2%minutes}, until slightly
burst. Add the green beans and cook, tossing, for a minutes or two, until
green beans are crisp-tender. Add the garlic and half the parsley and cook for
~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Set aside.

Once the potatoes are done, slice into 1⁄2 inch rounds and crush with the side
of your #knife{}.

In the same pan you cooked the tomatoes in, heat 1 tablespoon oil in a pan over
medium heat. Add the potatoes and cook for about ~{3%minutes} on each side,
until golden brown and crispy. Sprinkle with the remaining parsley and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.